===Etymology===
Middle English [[verray]] "true", from Old French [[verai]], [[vrai]], from Vulgar Latin ''*veracus'', derived from Latin [[verax]] "true".

===Adverb===
'''very'''

# to a [[high]] [[degree]]
#:''You're very tall.''
# [[true]], [[truly]]
#:''He tried his very best.''
#:''It was a very unique experience.'' (nonstandard)

